.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH mcp 1  "mcp " 
.SH NAME
mcp \- Run an MCP (Model Context Protocol) stdio server for AI agents
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmurk mcp\fR [\fB\-\-vault\fR] [\fB\-\-allow\-exec\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Run an MCP (Model Context Protocol) stdio server for AI agents
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-vault\fR \fI<VAULT>\fR [default: .murk]
Vault filename
.TP
\fB\-\-allow\-exec\fR
Enable the murk_exec tool (run commands with scoped secrets injected). Off by default: it runs arbitrary commands as this user — the injected secrets are grant\-scoped, but the command itself is not sandboxed
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
